    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sensitivity analysis: material properties and contact friction on QoI",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analyses were conducted varying cortical bone modulus (±15%), Ti-6Al-4V yield strength (±5%), polyaxial head friction coefficient (0.1–0.4), and rod diameter tolerance (±0.05 mm). Construct stiffness showed highest sensitivity to rod diameter tolerance (normalized sensitivity index 0.41) and bone modulus (0.33), while yield force was most sensitive to screw shank diameter and Ti-6Al-4V yield strength; friction coefficient effects on all three QoIs remained below 8% across the full range, confirming that the deterministic nominal-property model captures dominant variance sources."
  },
