      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw applicability constraint",
      "description": "This credibility assessment applies exclusively to solid (non-cannulated) pedicle screws manufactured from Ti-6Al-4V ELI per ASTM F136, with outer diameter 7.0–8.0 mm, used in a bilateral two-rod thoracolumbar construct. It does not apply to cannulated screws, cortical trajectory screws, screws in osteoporotic bone models, or screws subjected to fatigue or dynamic loading. The FEA material model (bilinear isotropic hardening) has been validated only against monotonic quasi-static loading; cyclic or impact loading scenarios are explicitly out of scope."
    }
  },
