      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Continuum FEA with bilinear isotropic hardening (Ti-6Al-4V) and linear elastic bone surrogate (UHMWPE per ASTM F1717) is the established model form for this class of implant V&V. Contact between screw and polyaxial head modeled with penalty method (friction coefficient 0.25 per literature). Geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-displacement regime. Model form selection justified by prior FDA guidance (ASME V&V 40 2018 §5.3) and published literature benchmarks. Simplifications (no fatigue damage, no viscoelasticity) are appropriate for quasi-static monotonic loading within the declared envelope.",
