      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab1 n=6, Lab2 n=5). All constructs assembled from production-representative hardware (same lot as clinical devices). Sample size provides 80% power to detect a 10% QoI difference at α=0.05 based on historical CV of 4–5%. Inter-laboratory variability assessed; pooled CV 4.5% confirms reproducibility. Coverage gaps acknowledged: only one screw diameter (7.5 mm) and one rod diameter (5.5 mm) tested; extrapolation to other sizes requires additional validation.",
