      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single set of ASTM F1717 conditions (5 mm/min quasi-static, ambient temperature, dry). The operating envelope bounds displacement rate to quasi-static only, but only one rate was tested. This represents a shortfall of one gradation relative to the required level 3. The shortfall is mitigated by: (1) the declared operating envelope explicitly restricts use to quasi-static loading, (2) sensitivity analysis confirms QoI insensitivity to rate variation within the quasi-static regime (±20% rate change produces <1% QoI change), and (3) the conservative acceptance bound (<10% QoI difference) provides additional margin. A detailed offset rationale is provided in the decision record.",
